{
  "stem": "21788.1",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[TONE]",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My name is Erwin Chaim, E-R-W-I-N, Chaim, C-H-A-I-M, pronounced Chaim.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In Germany, it was 'khime.' In Jewish, it's 'hi-am,' 'to life.'",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was born in 1928, the 23rd of May.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I am 68.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Not that I know of.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was born in Berlin, Germany, right in the middle of the city, close to Alexanderplatz, which is the center of town.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "By a coincident, I just started reading and finished it.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "This book, a rather heavy book, called by Claire Rayner.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And it kind of starts and describes the Jewish history, starting with the destruction of the Second Temple in the year 70 of the Common Era.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And she kind of sums up the instructions, or rather the beginning of these two families. 'And so it was that the wandering began.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It would be almost another 2,000 years before some of the descendants of Tamar and Susannah, by then split into many family lines, would meet again in the remote, cold, northern island of England, as three tributaries of the main river of the wandering Jew. 2,000 years or fear and hunger, as well as peace and plenty. 2,000 Years of stubbornly holding on to their faith, however painful non-believers made that devotion. 2,000 years of suffering, of striving, and above all, of survival.' And now, here I am, 2,000 years later, 1996, telling my story of our survival, of escaping out of Nazi Germany.",
      "word_count": 104
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My father's name was Henry Chaim, Heinrich in Germany.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Henry actually changes kind of to Henry here.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Heinrich, H-E-I-N-R-I-C-H, Heinrich Chaim, 'khime.'",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "He was a dentist.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My father was a very pleasant man.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He married my mother in 1927, and I came along in 1928.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he also joined the army in the First World War.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
